Subject: [PATCH 041/117] perf(tmux): cache hidden env var reads with 30s
 per-key TTL

Reduce subprocess spawns during polling by caching get_hidden_env()
results. The hot path (build_exclusion_set) was spawning tmux
show-environment on every poll cycle (2-60s adaptive interval) for
each active session.

Cache design:
- Per-key TTL (30s) via static RwLock<EnvCache>, harmonized with the
  existing SESSION_CACHE pattern in tmux/mod.rs
- Only positive hits cached (no negative caching) so newly-set
  variables are picked up immediately
- Write-through invalidation: set/remove/clear_all invalidate the
  relevant cache entries after successful tmux mutation
- get_hidden_env_batch also populates cache on success
