From: =?UTF-8?q?J=C3=A9r=C3=B4me=20Benoit?= <jerome.benoit@piment-noir.org>
Date: Sat, 7 Mar 2026 18:12:38 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 042/117] fix(session): coordinate deferred capture and poller
 via CaptureGate

For agents like opencode that require both a deferred capture thread
(to discover the initial session ID) and continuous polling (to detect
later changes), both threads previously ran concurrently -- creating a
race on the non-atomic load/mutate/save cycle in persist_session_to_storage.

Introduce CaptureGate (Condvar + Mutex) so the poller blocks until
the deferred capture completes, then uses the captured ID as its
initial_known value. This eliminates the TOCTOU on storage JSON,
redundant parallel work, and exclusion set inconsistency.

Ultraworked with [Sisyphus](https://github.com/code-yeongyu/oh-my-opencode)

Co-authored-by: Sisyphus <clio-agent@sisyphuslabs.ai>
