Subject: [PATCH 049/117] fix: prevent TUI freeze on dead pane re-entry by
 restarting on owned Instance

attach_session() was cloning the Instance, calling start_with_size_opts()
on the clone, then dropping it. SessionPoller::Drop called handle.join()
which blocked the TUI thread for 5-35s while the CaptureGate condvar
waited for deferred capture to complete.

Replace the clone+start pattern with restart_with_size_opts() on the
Home-owned Instance (via instance_map). restart_with_size_opts() properly
stops the old poller and joins deferred capture before spawning new
threads, so no blocking Drop occurs. The instances vec is synced by the
reload() call after tmux attach returns.
