Subject: [PATCH 052/117] fix: propagate session ID from poller to in-memory
 Instance via channel

SessionPoller was the only background thread using a fire-and-forget
callback instead of an mpsc channel to communicate results back to
the TUI. The on_change callback wrote agent_session_id to disk via
persist_session_to_storage(), but never updated the in-memory Instance.
Any subsequent TUI save() would overwrite the disk value with None.

Add result_tx/result_rx channel pair to SessionPoller, matching the
pattern used by StatusPoller, DeletionPoller, and CreationPoller.
The poller thread now sends (instance_id, session_id) on every change.
HomeView::apply_session_id_updates() drains the channel each tick,
updates both self.instances and self.instance_map, then persists.

Also adds retroactive capture in acquire_session_id() as a fallback
for sessions created before the poller was available, and splits
maybe_start_poller() to accept an explicit launch time so resumed
sessions (TUI restart) poll without a time filter.

Consolidates all raw save_with_groups calls through self.save().
