Subject: [PATCH 057/117] fix(session): persist deferred-capture session IDs
 via TUI gate drain and retroactive capture

Three bugs prevented session IDs from reaching sessions.json for non-Claude agents:

1. OpenCode new launch: deferred capture signaled CaptureGate but the
   poller seeded last_known from it, so the first poll saw no change and
   never forwarded the ID to the TUI thread.

2. Codex/Gemini/Vibe new launch: deferred capture signaled the gate but
   no poller existed (guard only matches claude|opencode), so the gate
   result was never consumed.

3. Codex/Gemini/Vibe TUI relaunch with None ID: no poller started, no
   discovery mechanism existed for pre-existing sessions.

Fix: add CaptureGate::try_take() for non-blocking drain, have
apply_session_id_updates() drain completed gates directly (keeping the
TUI-thread-only disk write invariant), and call try_retroactive_capture()
for codex/gemini/vibe at TUI startup. Also preserve agent_session_id
across reload() with .or() semantics and add immediate first poll for
gateless sessions.

