From: =?UTF-8?q?J=C3=A9r=C3=B4me=20Benoit?= <jerome.benoit@sap.com>
Date: Sat, 14 Mar 2026 13:25:42 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 100/117] feat(session): add Claude disk scan fallback via
 SessionPoller

Claude's /clear and /new commands don't fire hooks, so session_id changes
go undetected. Add scan_claude_session_from_disk() which reads
~/.claude/projects/{encoded-path}/*.jsonl to find the most recently
modified UUID session file. Wire it through claude_poll_fn() into the
existing SessionPoller, matching the same pattern as OpenCode.
